# Error Handling

- Never swallow exceptions silently.
- Backend: map known errors to explicit HTTP exceptions; keep unknowns as internal errors.
- Frontend: surface user-safe messages and keep technical details in logs/observability tooling.
- Preserve useful context in error payloads/logs (`type`, `id`, `duration`, `message`).
- Keep error responses consistent with global exception filter output shape.
